msgctxt "MixedModelsBOptions|"
msgid "Number of iterations reserved for burnin."
msgstr "Jumlah iterasi disajikan untuk burnin."

msgctxt "MixedModelsBOptions|"
msgid "Number of MCMC samples."
msgstr "Jumlah sampel MCMC."

msgctxt "MixedModelsBOptions|"
msgid "Number of MCMC chains."
msgstr "Jumlah rantai MCMC."

msgctxt "MixedModelsBOptions|"
msgid ""
"Average target proposal acceptance of each step. Increasing Adapt delta "
"results in better-behaved chains, but also longer fitting times."
msgstr ""
"Penerimaan proposal target rata-rata dari setiap langkah. Meningkatkan delta "
"Adaptasi menghasilkan rantai berperilaku lebih baik, tetapi juga waktu "
"penyesuaian lebih lama."

msgctxt "MixedModelsBOptions|"
msgid ""
"The cap for the number of trees evaluated during each iteration. Prevents "
"excessively long execution times."
msgstr ""
"Kap untuk jumlah pohon dievaluasikan selama setiap iterasi. Mencegah waktu "
"perjalanan lama secara lampau."

msgctxt "MixedModelsBOptions|"
msgid "Specifies the content of the default output table."
msgstr "Menentukan konten dari tabel luaran bawaan."

msgctxt "MixedModelsBOptions|"
msgid ""
"A table for each fixed effects term will be created in the default output "
"and it will show the differences from the grand mean for each of the levels "
"of the terms (or one standard deviation distance for continuous terms). This "
"option is selected by default."
msgstr ""
"Tabel untuk setiap istilah efek tetap akan dibuat di luaran bawaan dan itu "
"akan menampilkan perbedaan dari rerata besar untuk setiap tingkat istilah "
"(atau satu jarak deviasi standar untuk istilah berkelanjutan). Opsi ini "
"dipilih secara bawaan."

msgctxt "MixedModelsBOptions|"
msgid ""
"A table for each fixed effects term will be created in the default output "
"and it will show the estimated marginal mean for each of the levels of the "
"terms (or one standard deviation distance for continuous terms)."
msgstr ""
"Tabel untuk setiap istilah efek tetap akan dibuat di luaran bawaan dan itu "
"akan menampilkan rerata margin terestimasi untuk setiap tingkat istilah "
"(atau satu jarak deviasi standar untuk istilah berkelanjutan)."

msgctxt "MixedModelsBOptions|"
msgid "Adds an output table including relevant fit statistics."
msgstr "Menambahkan tabel luaran menyertakan statistik penyesuaian relevan."

msgctxt "MixedModelsBOptions|"
msgid "Shows the estimated fixed effect coefficients."
msgstr "Menampilkan koefisien efek tetap terestimasi."

msgctxt "MixedModelsBOptions|"
msgid ""
"Shows the estimated residual variances and variances/correlations of random "
"effects coefficients."
msgstr ""
"Menampilkan varians residu terestimasi dan varians/korelasi dari koefisien "
"efek acak."

msgctxt "MixedModelsBOptions|"
msgid "Shows the estimated random effects coefficients."
msgstr "Menampilkan koefisien efek acak terestimasi."

msgctxt "MixedModelsBOptions|"
msgid ""
"Width of the credible interval. Set at 95% by default, which can be changed "
"by the user."
msgstr ""
"Lebar interval kredibel. Diatur ke 95% secara bawaan, yang dapat diubah oleh "
"pengguna."

msgctxt "MixedModelsMCMCDiagnostics|"
msgid "Fixed effects model terms whose MCMC chains can be diagnosed."
msgstr "Istilah model efek tetap yang rantai MCMC dapat didiagnosa."

msgctxt "MixedModelsMCMCDiagnostics|"
msgid "Fixed effects model term whose chain will be diagnosed."
msgstr "Istilah model efek tetap yang rantai dapat didiagnosa."

msgctxt "MixedModelsMCMCDiagnostics|"
msgid ""
"Fixed effects model term whose chain will be diagnosed. Only available if "
"the Plot type is Scatterplot."
msgstr ""
"Istilah model efek tetap yang rantai dapat didiagnosa. Hanya tersedia jika "
"jenis Diagram adalah Diagram Pencaran."

msgctxt "MixedModelsMCMCDiagnostics|"
msgid ""
"Different types of MCMC diagnostic plots. The plotted values correspond to "
"the fixed effect terms displayed in the default output. Those are the "
"deviations from the estimated grand mean by default, but can be changed to "
"estimated marginal means in the Options section."
msgstr ""
"Jenis diagram diagnostik MCMC berbeda. Nilai berdiagram sesuai dengan "
"istilah efek tetap ditampilkan di luaran bawaan. Itu adalah deviasi dari "
"rerata besar terestimasi secara bawaan, tetapi dapat diubah ke rerata margin "
"terestimasi di bagian Opsi."

msgctxt "MixedModelsMCMCDiagnostics|"
msgid "Traceplot of the individual chains."
msgstr "Diagram jejak dari rantai individu."

msgctxt "MixedModelsMCMCDiagnostics|"
msgid "Scatterplot of two model terms."
msgstr "Diagram pencaran dari dua istilah model."

msgctxt "MixedModelsMCMCDiagnostics|"
msgid "Histogram of the posterior samples."
msgstr "Histogram dari sampel posterior."

msgctxt "MixedModelsMCMCDiagnostics|"
msgid "Overlaid density plots of samples from each chain."
msgstr "Diagram kepadatan berlapis dari sampel dari setiap rantai."

msgctxt "MixedModelsMCMCDiagnostics|"
msgid "Average autocorrelation plots across all chains."
msgstr "Diagram korelasi otomatis rata-rata di seluruh rantai."

msgctxt "MixedModelsModel|"
msgid "All the fixed effects variables that can be included in the model."
msgstr "Semua variabel efek acak yang dapat disertakan dalam model."

msgctxt "MixedModelsModel|"
msgid ""
"The independent variables in the model. By default, all the main effects of "
"the specified independent variables and their interactions are included in "
"the model. To include more interactions, click multiple variables (e.g., by "
"holding the ctrl/cmd button on your keyboard while clicking) and drag those "
"into the Fixed effects box."
msgstr ""
"Variabel independen dalam model. Secara bawaan, semua efek utama dari "
"variabel independen tertentu dan interaksi mereka disertakan dalam model. "
"Untuk menyertakan lebih banyak interaksi, klik beberapa variabel (mis., "
"dengan menahan tombol ctrl/cmd pada papan ketik Anda ketika mengeklik) dan "
"seret itu ke dalam kotak efek Tetap."

msgctxt "MixedModelsModel|"
msgid "Include the intercept in the model."
msgstr "Sertakan intersep dalam model."

msgctxt "MixedModelsModel|"
msgid ""
"The random effects organized by random effects grouping factors. By default, "
"all of the random effects corresponding to the fixed effects are included "
"and JASP internally checks and removes non-estimable random effects. That "
"is, the default corresponds to the maximal random effects structure "
"justified by the design. Unticking the boxes on the left of the variable "
"names removes the random effect from the corresponding random effects "
"grouping factor."
msgstr ""
"Efek acak diorganisir oleh faktor penggrupan efek acak. Secara bawaan, semua "
"efek acak sesuai dengan efek tetap disertakan dan JASP secara internal "
"memeriksa dan menghapus efek acak tidak dapat diestimasi. Yaitu, bawaan "
"sesuai dengan struktur efek acak maksimal dibenarkan oleh rancangan. "
"Menghapus centang kotak pada kiri nama variabel menghapus efek acak dari "
"faktor penggrupan efek acak sesuai."

msgctxt "MixedModelsModel|"
msgid ""
"Specifies whether the correlations between the random effects parameters "
"within each random effects grouping factor should be estimated."
msgstr ""
"Menentukan apakah korelasi antara parameter efek acak dalam setiap faktor "
"penggrupan efek acak harus diestimasi."

msgctxt "MixedModelsOptions|"
msgid ""
"There are different types of sum of squares. The choice of the type is "
"important when there are multiple factors and when the data are unbalanced. "
"In an unbalanced design, the different levels of the independent variable do "
"not have an equal number of observations (e.g., one group contains more "
"observations than another group). In such cases, the sum of squares type can "
"influence the results."
msgstr ""
"Ada jenis berbeda jumlah kuadrat. Pilihan dari jenis penting ketika ada "
"beberapa faktor dan ketika data tidak seimbang. Dalam desain tidak seimbang, "
"tingkat berbeda dari variabel independen tidak memiliki angka sama dari "
"observasi (mis., satu grup berisi lebih banyak observasi dari grup lain). "
"Dalam kasus itu, jenis jumlah kuadrat dapat diinfluens hasil."

msgctxt "MixedModelsOptions|"
msgid ""
"Hierarchical/partially sequential sum of squares. It is the reduction of "
"error when each factor is added to a model that includes all the other "
"factors, except those in which the added factor is involved, such as "
"interactions containing it. Langsrud (2003) advises to apply this type for "
"an ANOVA with unbalanced data."
msgstr ""
"Jumlah sekuensial hierarkikal/sebagian kuadrat. Itu adalah reduksi galat "
"ketika setiap faktor ditambahkan ke model yang menyertakan semua faktor "
"lain, kecuali itu di mana faktor tertambah terlibat, seperti interaksi "
"berisi faktor itu. Langsrud (2003) menyarankan untuk menerapkan jenis ini "
"untuk ANOVA dengan data tidak seimbang."

msgctxt "MixedModelsOptions|"
msgid ""
"Partial sum of squares. It is the reduction of error when each factor is "
"added to a model that includes all the other factors, including interactions "
"with this factor. This type is often selected, because it takes interactions "
"into account (Langsrud, 2003). This type is selected by default and "
"recommended for designs in which the imbalance is not a consequence of "
"imbalance in the population, but due to random variation."
msgstr ""
"Jumlah parsial kuadrat. Itu adlaah reduksi galat ketika setiap faktor "
"ditambahkan ke model yang menyertakan semua faktor lain, menyertakan "
"interaksi dengan faktor ini. Jenis ini sering dipilih, karena itu "
"memperhitungkan interaksi (Langsrud, 2003). Jenis ini dipilih secara bawaan "
"dan direkomendasikan untuk rancangan di mana ketidakseimbangan bukan "
"konsekuensi ketidakseimbangan di populasi, tetapi karena variasi acak."

msgctxt "MixedModelsOptions|"
msgid ""
"Specifies whether the model intercept should be tested. Available only if "
"the likelihood ratio test or parametric bootstrap is selected in the Model "
"Terms test."
msgstr ""
"Menentukan apakah intersep model harus diuji. Tersedia hanya jika uji rasio "
"kemungkinan atau bootstrap parametris dipilih di uji Istilah Model."

msgctxt "MixedModelsOptions|"
msgid ""
"Methods for obtaining p-values for the ANOVA summary. Note that the Kenward-"
"Roger approximation for degrees of freedom can be very RAM and time "
"consuming with larger datasets and complicated random effects structures. "
"Several methods are available."
msgstr ""
"Metode untuk memperoleh nilai-p untuk ringkasan ANOVA. Dicatat bahwa "
"perkiraan Kenward-Roger untuk derajat kebebasan dapat RAM dan memakan waktu "
"dengan rangkaian data lebih besar dan struktur efek acak rumit. Beberapa "
"metode tersedia."

msgctxt "MixedModelsOptions|"
msgid "Specifies factor encoding for categorical variables."
msgstr "Menentukan pengenkodean faktor untuk variabel kategorikal."

msgctxt "MixedModelsOptions|"
msgid "Compares each category to the overall mean."
msgstr "Membandingkan setiap kategori dengan rerata keseluruhan."

msgctxt "MixedModelsOptions|"
msgid ""
"Compares each category to a baseline category, also known as 'Dummy' coding."
msgstr ""
"Membandingkan setiap kategori dengan kategori garis dasar, juga diketahui "
"sebagai pengkodean 'Dummy'."

msgctxt "MixedModelsOptions|"
msgid "Number of samples to be used for the parametric bootstrap."
msgstr "Jumlah sampel digunakan untuk bootstrap parametris."

msgctxt "MixedModelsOptions|"
msgid "Output table containing relevant statistics for the model."
msgstr "Tabel luaran berisi statistik relevan untuk model."

msgctxt "MixedModelsOptions|"
msgid "Shows the estimated fixed effect coefficients."
msgstr "Menampilkan koefisien efek tetap terestimasi."

msgctxt "MixedModelsOptions|"
msgid ""
"Shows the estimated residual variances and variances/correlations of random "
"effects coefficients."
msgstr ""
"Menampilkan varians residu terestimasi dan varians/korelasi dari koefisien "
"efek acak."

msgctxt "MixedModelsOptions|"
msgid "Shows the estimated random effects coefficients."
msgstr "Menampilkan koefisien efek acak terestimasi."

msgctxt "MixedModelsOptions|"
msgid ""
"Shows the maximum ratio of the likelihood of the obtained p-value under H1 "
"vs the likelihood of the obtained p value under H0. For example, if the two-"
"sided p-value equals .05, the Vovk-Sellke MPR equals 2.46, indicating that "
"this p-value is at most 2.46 times more likely to occur under H1 than under "
"H0."
msgstr ""
"Menampilkan rasio maksimum dari kemungkinan nilai-p terambil di bawah H1 vs "
"kemungkinan nilai p terambil di bawah H0. Contohnya, jika nilai-p dua arah "
"sama dengan .05, MPR Vovk-Sellke sama dengan 2.46, mengindikasikan bahwa "
"nilai-p ini kemungkinan lebih banyak 2.46 kali lebih besar terjadi di bawah "
"H1 dari di bawah H0."

msgctxt "MixedModelsPlots|"
msgid ""
"Categorical or ordinal fixed effects variables that can be used for "
"visualization."
msgstr ""
"Variabel efek tetap kategorikal atau ordinal yang dapat digunakan untuk "
"visualisasi."

msgctxt "MixedModelsPlots|"
msgid "Variables that will be plotted on the horizontal axis."
msgstr "Variabel yang akan didiagramkan pada sumbu horizontal."

msgctxt "MixedModelsPlots|"
msgid ""
"Variables that will be plotted inside the plot as different traces/lines."
msgstr ""
"Variabel yang akan didiagramkan di dalam diagram sebagai jejak/garis berbeda."

msgctxt "MixedModelsPlots|"
msgid "Variables whose levels will be split across different plots."
msgstr "Variabel yang tingkat akan dipisahkan di seluruh diagram berbeda."

msgctxt "MixedModelsPlots|"
msgid ""
"Random effect grouping factors that can be used for data aggregation of "
"background data."
msgstr ""
"Faktor penggrupan efek acak yang dapat digunakan untuk agregasi data dari "
"data latar belakang."

msgctxt "MixedModelsPlots|"
msgid ""
"The level of aggregation for the response variable. i.e., if participants "
"are selected, the individual data points in the background are their "
"averages across the combinations of levels of fixed effect factors selected "
"in the Horizontal axis, Separate lines, and Separate plots."
msgstr ""
"Tingkat agregasi untuk variabel tanggapan. Yaitu, jika peserta dipilih, "
"titik data individu di latar belakang adalah rata-rata mereka di seluruh "
"kombinasi tingkat dari faktor efek tetap dipilih di sumbu Horizontal, Garis "
"terpisah, dan Diagram terpisah."

msgctxt "MixedModelsPlots|"
msgid ""
"Type of standard error on which the error bars will be based. Default is "
"'model', which plots model-based standard errors. Several options are "
"available."
msgstr ""
"Jenis galat standar di mana batang galat akan didasarkan. Bawaannya adalah "
"'model', yang mendiagramkan galat standar berbasis model. Beberapa opsi "
"tersedia."

msgctxt "MixedModelsPlots|"
msgid ""
"Width of the confidence interval. Set at 95% by default, which can be "
"changed by the user."
msgstr ""
"Lebar interval kepercayaan. Diatur ke 95% secara bawaan, yang dapat diubah "
"oleh pengguna."

msgctxt "MixedModelsPlots|"
msgid ""
"How the factor levels should be distinguished. This can be by color, shape, "
"linetype, or fill."
msgstr ""
"Bagaimana tingkat faktor harus dibedakan. Ini dapat berupa warna, bentuk, "
"jenis garis, atau isian."

msgctxt "MixedModelsPlots|"
msgid ""
"Type of background element to be used on the plots. Several options are "
"available."
msgstr ""
"Jenis elemen latar belakang digunakan pada diagram. Beberapa opsi tersedia."

msgctxt "MixedModelsPlots|"
msgid "Transparency level of the plotted elements (geoms)."
msgstr "Tingkat transparansi dari elemen berdiagram (geoms)."

msgctxt "MixedModelsPlots|"
msgid "Width of the jitter."
msgstr "Lebar getaran."

msgctxt "MixedModelsPlots|"
msgid "Height of the jitter."
msgstr "Tinggi getaran."

msgctxt "MixedModelsPlots|"
msgid "Width of the element."
msgstr "Lebar elemen."

msgctxt "MixedModelsPlots|"
msgid "Spacing between the plotted elements (geoms)."
msgstr "Jarak antara elemen berdiagram (geoms)."

msgctxt "MixedModelsPlots|"
msgid ""
"Color palette to be used on the plot display. Several options are available."
msgstr ""
"Palet warna yang digunakan pada tampilan diagram. Beberapa opsi tersedia."

msgctxt "MixedModelsPlots|"
msgid ""
"Whether and where should the legend be plotted. Several options are "
"available."
msgstr "Apakah dan di mana legenda harus didiagramkan. Beberapa opsi tersedia."

msgctxt "MixedModelsPlots|"
msgid "No legend is plotted."
msgstr "Tidak ada legenda didiagramkan."

msgctxt "MixedModelsPlots|"
msgid "The legend is plotted on the bottom."
msgstr "Legenda didiagramkan di bawah."

msgctxt "MixedModelsPlots|"
msgid "The legend is plotted on the right."
msgstr "Legenda didiagramkan di kanan."

msgctxt "MixedModelsPlots|"
msgid "The legend is plotted on the top."
msgstr "Legenda didiagramkan di atas."

msgctxt "MixedModelsPlots|"
msgid "The legend is plotted on the left."
msgstr "Legenda didiagramkan di kiri."

msgctxt "MixedModelsPlots|"
msgid ""
"Color of the aggregated response variable. Several options are available."
msgstr "Warna dari variabel tanggapan teragregasi. Beberapa opsi tersedia."

msgctxt "MixedModelsPlots|"
msgid "Relative size of the plotted text."
msgstr "Ukuran teks berdiagram relatif."

msgctxt "MixedModelsPlots|"
msgid "Relative size of the foreground data (confidence interval bars, etc.)."
msgstr "Ukuran data latar depan relatif (batang interval kepercayaan, dll.)."

msgctxt "MixedModelsPlots|"
msgid "Display numerical summary of the plotted objects."
msgstr "Tampilkan ringkasan objek berdiagram numerik."

msgctxt "MixedModelsBGLMM|"
msgid ""
"Bayesian Generalized Linear Mixed Models allow you to model a linear "
"relationship between one or more explanatory variable(s) and a dependent "
"variable in cases where the observations are not independent, but clustered "
"within one or several random effects grouping factors (e.g., repeated "
"measures across participants or items, children within schools). They are "
"generalizations of Bayesian Linear Mixed Models and allow you to model "
"response variables that are not continuous using different likelihoods and "
"link functions."
msgstr ""
"Model Bercampur Linear Tergeneralisasi Bayes mengizinkan Anda untuk "
"memodelkan hubungan linear antara satu atau lebih variabel penjelasan dan "
"variabel dependen dalam kasus di mana observasi tidak independen, tetapi "
"diklaster dalam satu atau beberapa faktor penggrupan efek acak (mis., "
"pengukuran berulang di seluruh peserta atau item, anak-anak dalam sekolah). "
"Mereka adalah generalisasi Model Bercampur Linear Bayes dan mengizinkan Anda "
"untuk memodelkan variabel tanggapan yang tidak berkelanjutan menggunakan "
"kemungkinan berbeda dan fungsi tautan."

msgctxt "MixedModelsBGLMM|"
msgid "Assumptions"
msgstr "Asumsi"

msgctxt "MixedModelsBGLMM|"
msgid ""
"Linearity and additivity: The response variable is related to all predictors "
"according to the link function and the effects of the predictors are "
"additive on the linear scale."
msgstr ""
"Linearitas dan penambahan: Variabel tanggapan terkait dengan semua prediktor "
"menurut fungsi tautan dan efek prediktor aditif pada skala linear."

msgctxt "MixedModelsBGLMM|"
msgid ""
"Independence of errors: The errors are uncorrelated with each other after "
"taking the model (i.e., fixed effects and random effects structure) into "
"account."
msgstr ""
"Independen dari galat: Galat tidak dikorelasikan satu sama lain setelah "
"mengambil model (yaitu, efek tetap dan struktur efek acak) diperhitungkan."

msgctxt "MixedModelsBGLMM|"
msgid ""
"Homoscedasticity: The error variance of each predictor is constant across "
"all values of that predictor."
msgstr ""
"Homosedastisitas: Varians galat dari setiap prediktor konstan di seluruh "
"nilai prediktor itu."

msgctxt "MixedModelsBGLMM|"
msgid ""
"Distribution of errors: The errors are distributed according to the "
"distributional family."
msgstr ""
"Distribusi dari galat: Galat didistribusikan menurut keluarga distribusional."

msgctxt "MixedModelsBGLMM|"
msgid ""
"The analysis uses orthonormal contrasts such that the marginal prior on all "
"fixed effects is identical for categorical (nominal and ordinal) predictors "
"(R uses dummy encoding by default). This scheme is used for better "
"interpretability of models with interactions. However, the fixed and random "
"effect estimates will differ from those obtained from R with default "
"settings. We advise using the 'Estimated marginal means' section for "
"obtaining mean estimates at individual factor levels. For comparing the mean "
"estimates, use the contrasts option."
msgstr ""
"Analisis menggunakan kontras ortonormal sedemikian rupa priori margin pada "
"semua efek tetap identik untuk prediktor (R menggunakan pengenkodean dummy "
"secara bawaan) kategorikal (nominal dan ordinal). Skema ini digunakan untuk "
"interpretabilitas lebih baik dari model dengan interaksi. Namun, estimasi "
"efek tetap dan acak akan berbeda dari itu diperoleh dari R dengan pengaturan "
"bawaan. Kami menyarankan menggunakan bagian 'Rerata margin terestimasi' "
"untuk memperoleh estimasi rerata di tingkat faktor individu. Untuk "
"membandingkan estimasi rerata, gunakan opsi kontras."

msgctxt "MixedModelsBGLMM|"
msgid "The analysis uses a long data format."
msgstr "Analisis menggunakan format data panjang."

msgctxt "MixedModelsBGLMM|"
msgid ""
"The prior distributions are weakly informative and should be well-behaved in "
"parameter estimation settings. The module uses the default prior "
"distribution settings of the rstanarm R package which defines "
"normal(location = 0, scale = 2.5) prior distributions on scaled and centered "
"model coefficients."
msgstr ""
"Distribusi priori secara lemah informatif dan harus diperlakukan dengan baik "
"di pengaturan estimasi parameter. Modul menggunakan pengaturan distribusi "
"priori bawaan dari paket R rstanarm yang mendefinisikan distribusi priori "
"normal(lokasi = 0, scale = 2.5) pada koefisien model terskala dan terpusat."

msgctxt "MixedModelsBGLMM|"
msgid "Dependent (response) variable."
msgstr "Variabel dependen (tanggapan)."

msgctxt "MixedModelsBGLMM|"
msgid ""
"Number of trials, only applicable if the Binomial (aggregated) family is "
"selected."
msgstr ""
"Jumlah percobaan, hanya dapat diterapkan jika keluarga Binomial "
"(teragregasi) dipilih."

msgctxt "MixedModelsBGLMM|"
msgid ""
"Variables used as the fixed effects predictors (the model terms can be "
"specified under Model section). These are usually the variables of primary "
"scientific interest."
msgstr ""
"Variabel digunakan sebagai prediktor efek tetap (istilah model dapat "
"ditentukan di bawah bagian Model). Ini biasanya variabel dari fokus utama "
"saintifik."

msgctxt "MixedModelsBGLMM|"
msgid ""
"Categorical variable(s) specifying clusters of observations (i.e., several "
"observations per level of a random effects grouping factor). These are "
"typically variables, such as participants or items, one wants to generalize "
"over. Factors with very few levels (i.e., fewer than five or six levels) "
"should not be used as random effects grouping factors as the number of "
"levels determines the power of the fixed effects tests (Westfall, Kenny, & "
"Judd, 2014). The random effects structure (i.e., random intercepts, random "
"slopes, and correlations among random effects parameters) can be specified "
"under Model - Random effects. The default random effects structure is the "
"automatically determined 'maximal random effects structure justified by the "
"design' (Barr, Levy, Scheepers, & Tily, 2013)."
msgstr ""
"Variabel kategorikal menentukan klaster observasi (yaitu, beberapa observasi "
"per tingkat dari faktor penggrupan efek acak). Ini adalah secara umum "
"variabel, seperti peserta atau item, yang ingin generalisasi. Faktor dengan "
"tingkat sangat sedikit (yaitu, lebih sedikit dari lima atau enam tingkat) "
"tidak harus digunakan sebagai faktor penggrupan efek acak karena jumlah "
"tingkat menentukan kekuatan uji efek tetap (Westfall, Kenny, & Judd, 2014). "
"Struktur efek acak (yaitu, intersep acak, corong acak, dan korelasi si "
"antara parameter efek acak) dapat ditentukan di bawah Model - Efek acak. "
"Struktur efek acak bawaan secara otomatis 'maksimal struktur efek acak "
"maksimal dibenarkan oleh rancangan' ditentukan (Barr, Levy, Scheepers, & "
"Tily, 2013)."

msgctxt "MixedModelsBGLMM|"
msgid ""
"Distribution function whose likelihood will be used for the dependent "
"variable. Several options are available."
msgstr ""
"Fungsi distribusi yang kemungkinan akan digunakan untuk variabel dependen. "
"Beberapa opsi tersedia."

msgctxt "MixedModelsBGLMM|"
msgid ""
"Link function that will be used to model the mean parameter of the selected "
"distribution function."
msgstr ""
"Fungsi tautan yang akan digunakan untuk memodelkan parameter rerata dari "
"fungsi distribusi terpilih."

msgctxt "MixedModelsBGLMM|"
msgid ""
"Fixed effects variables that can be used for computing estimated marginal "
"means."
msgstr ""
"Variabel efek tetap yang dapat digunakan untuk menghitung rerata margin "
"terestimasi."

msgctxt "MixedModelsBGLMM|"
msgid "Variables for which the estimated marginal means will be computed."
msgstr "Variabel untuk mana rerata margin terestimasi akan dihitung."

msgctxt "MixedModelsBGLMM|"
msgid ""
"Width of the confidence interval. Set at 95% by default, which can be "
"changed by the user."
msgstr ""
"Lebar interval kepercayaan. Diatur ke 95% secara bawaan, yang dapat diubah "
"oleh pengguna."

msgctxt "MixedModelsBGLMM|"
msgid ""
"Specifies the 'levels' of continuous variables (expressed in standard "
"deviations) for which the estimated marginal means are computed."
msgstr ""
"Menentukan 'tingkat' dari variabel berkelanjutan (diungkapkan di deviasi "
"standar) yang mana rerata margin terestimasi dihitung."

msgctxt "MixedModelsBGLMM|"
msgid ""
"Whether the estimated marginal means should be computed on the response "
"scale or untransformed linear scale. The response scale is selected by "
"default."
msgstr ""
"Apakah rerata margin terestimasi harus dihitung pada skala tanggapan atau "
"skala linear tidak bertransform. Skala tanggapan dipilih secara bawaan."

msgctxt "MixedModelsBGLMM|"
msgid ""
"Creates a table for specifying contrasts based on the estimated marginal "
"means. The first column contains row indices corresponding to the estimated "
"marginal means output table. Columns with variable names show the levels of "
"each variable for the respective marginal mean. Columns labeled ‘Contrast x’ "
"are used to define contrasts. To specify a contrast between two marginal "
"means, enter -1 and 1 in the corresponding rows. Interactions can be tested "
"by defining differences in marginal means of one variable across levels of "
"another."
msgstr ""
"Membuat tabel untuk menentukan kontras berdasarkan rerata margin "
"terestimasi. Kolom pertama berisi indeks baris sesuai dengan tabel luaran "
"rerata margin terestimasi. Kolom dengan nama variabel menampilkan tingkat "
"dari setiap variabel untuk rerata margin masing-masing. Kolom dilabeli "
"‘Kontras x’ digunakan untuk mendefinisikan kontras. Untuk menentukan kontras "
"antara dua rerata margin, masukkan -1 dan 1 di baris sesuai. Interaksi dapat "
"diuji dengan mendefinisikan perbedaan di rerata margin dari satu variabel di "
"seluruh tingkat lain."

msgctxt "MixedModelsBGLMM|"
msgid "Continuous variables"
msgstr "Variabel berkelanjutan"

msgctxt "MixedModelsBGLMM|"
msgid ""
"Continuous fixed effects variables that can be used for estimating the "
"conditional slopes."
msgstr ""
"Variabel efek tetap berkelanjutan yang dapat digunakan untuk mengestimasi "
"corong kondisional."

msgctxt "MixedModelsBGLMM|"
msgid "Variables for which the estimated conditional slopes will be computed."
msgstr "Variabel yang mana corong kondisional terestimasi akan dihitung."

msgctxt "MixedModelsBGLMM|"
msgid ""
"Fixed effects variables over which the conditional slopes can be computed."
msgstr "Variabel efek tetap di mana corong kondisional dapat dihitung."

msgctxt "MixedModelsBGLMM|"
msgid "Variables over which the conditional slopes will be computed."
msgstr "Variabel di mana corong kondisional akan dihitung."

msgctxt "MixedModelsBGLMM|"
msgid ""
"Specifies the 'levels' of continuous variables (expressed in standard "
"deviations) over which the conditional slopes are computed."
msgstr ""
"Menentukan 'tingkat' dari variabel berkelanjutan (diungkapkan di deviasi "
"standar) di mana corong kondisional dihitung."

msgctxt "MixedModelsBGLMM|"
msgid ""
"Creates a table for specifying contrasts based on the estimated conditional "
"slopes. The first column contains row indices corresponding to the estimated "
"conditional slopes output table. Columns with variable names show the levels "
"of each variable for the respective conditional slope. Columns labeled "
"‘Contrast x’ are used to define contrasts. To specify a contrast between two "
"conditional slopes, enter -1 and 1 in the corresponding rows. Interactions "
"can be tested by defining differences in conditional slopes of one variable "
"across levels of another."
msgstr ""
"Membuat tabel untuk menentukan kontras berdasarkan corong kondisional "
"terestimasi. Kolom pertama berisi indeks baris sesuai dengan tabel luaran "
"corong kondisional terestimasi. Kolom dengan nama variabel menampilkan "
"tingkat dari setiap variabel untuk corong kondisional masing-masing. Kolom "
"dilabeli ‘Kontras x’ digunakan untuk menentukan kontras. Untuk menentukan "
"kontras antara dua corong kondisional, masukkan -1 dan 1 di baris sesuai. "
"Interaksi dapat diuji dengan mendefinisikan perbedaan di corong kondisional "
"dari satu variabel di seluruh tingkat lain."

msgctxt "MixedModelsBLMM|"
msgid ""
"Bayesian Linear Mixed Models allow you to model a linear relationship "
"between one or more explanatory variable(s) and a continuous dependent "
"variable in cases where the observations are not independent, but clustered "
"within one or several random effects grouping factors (e.g., repeated "
"measures across participants or items, children within schools). An "
"introduction to this model class and the concepts introduced below is "
"provided in Singmann and Kellen (2019)."
msgstr ""
"Model Bercampur Linear Bayes mengizinkan Anda untuk memodelkan hubungan "
"linear antara satu atau lebih variabel penjelasan dan variabel dependen "
"berkelanjutan dalam kasus di mana observasi tidak independen, tetapi "
"diklaster dalam satu atau beberapa faktor penggrupan efek acak (mis., "
"pengukuran berulang di seluruh peserta atau item, anak-anak dalam sekolah). "
"Pengenalan kelas model ini dan konsep dikenalkan di bawah disediakan di "
"Singmann dan Kellen (2019)."

msgctxt "MixedModelsBLMM|"
msgid "Assumptions"
msgstr "Asumsi"

msgctxt "MixedModelsBLMM|"
msgid "Continuous response variable."
msgstr "Variabel tanggapan berkelanjutan."

msgctxt "MixedModelsBLMM|"
msgid ""
"Linearity and additivity: The response variable is linearly related to all "
"predictors and the effects of the predictors are additive."
msgstr ""
"Linearitas dan penambahan: Variabel tanggapan secara linear terkait dengan "
"semua prediktor dan efek prediktor aditif."

msgctxt "MixedModelsBLMM|"
msgid ""
"Independence of errors: The errors are uncorrelated with each other after "
"taking the model (i.e., fixed effects and random effects structure) into "
"account."
msgstr ""
"Independen dari galat: Galat tidak dikorelasikan satu sama lain setelah "
"mengambil model (yaitu, efek tetap dan struktur efek acak) diperhitungkan."

msgctxt "MixedModelsBLMM|"
msgid ""
"Homoscedasticity: The error variance of each predictor is constant across "
"all values of that predictor."
msgstr ""
"Homosedastisitas: Varians galat dari setiap prediktor konstan di seluruh "
"nilai prediktor itu."

msgctxt "MixedModelsBLMM|"
msgid ""
"Normality of errors: The errors are normally distributed with mean zero."
msgstr ""
"Normalitas dari galat: Galat secara normal didistribusikan dengan rerata nol."

msgctxt "MixedModelsBLMM|"
msgid ""
"The analysis uses orthonormal contrasts such that the marginal prior on all "
"fixed effects is identical for categorical (nominal and ordinal) predictors "
"(R uses dummy encoding by default). This scheme is used for better "
"interpretability of models with interactions. However, the fixed and random "
"effects estimates will differ from those obtained from R with default "
"settings. We advise using the 'Estimated marginal means' section for "
"obtaining mean estimates at individual factor levels. For comparing the mean "
"estimates, use the contrasts option."
msgstr ""
"Analisis menggunakan kontras ortonormal sedemikian rupa priori margin pada "
"semua efek tetap identik untuk prediktor (R menggunakan pengenkodean dummy "
"secara bawaan) kategorikal (nominal dan ordinal). Skema ini digunakan untuk "
"interpretabilitas lebih baik dari model dengan interaksi. Namun, estimasi "
"efek tetap dan acak akan berbeda dari itu diperoleh dari R dengan pengaturan "
"bawaan. Kami menyarankan menggunakan bagian 'Rerata margin terestimasi' "
"untuk memperoleh estimasi rerata di tingkat faktor individu. Untuk "
"membandingkan estimasi rerata, gunakan opsi kontras."

msgctxt "MixedModelsBLMM|"
msgid "The analysis uses a long data format."
msgstr "Analisis menggunakan format data panjang."

msgctxt "MixedModelsBLMM|"
msgid ""
"The prior distributions are weakly informative and should be well-behaved in "
"parameter estimation settings. The module uses the default prior "
"distribution settings of the rstanarm R package which defines "
"normal(location = 0, scale = 2.5) prior distributions on scaled and centered "
"model coefficients."
msgstr ""
"Distribusi priori secara lemah informatif dan harus diperlakukan dengan baik "
"di pengaturan estimasi parameter. Modul menggunakan pengaturan distribusi "
"priori bawaan dari paket R rstanarm yang mendefinisikan distribusi priori "
"normal(lokasi = 0, scale = 2.5) pada koefisien model terskala dan terpusat."

msgctxt "MixedModelsBLMM|"
msgid "Dependent (response) variable."
msgstr "Variabel dependen (tanggapan)."

msgctxt "MixedModelsBLMM|"
msgid ""
"Variables used as the fixed effects predictors (the model terms can be "
"specified under Model section). These are usually the variables of primary "
"scientific interest."
msgstr ""
"Variabel digunakan sebagai prediktor efek tetap (istilah model dapat "
"ditentukan di bawah bagian Model). Ini biasanya variabel dari fokus utama "
"saintifik."

msgctxt "MixedModelsBLMM|"
msgid ""
"Categorical variable(s) specifying clusters of observations (i.e., several "
"observations per level of a random effects grouping factor). These are "
"typically variables, such as participants or items, one wants to generalize "
"over. Factors with very few levels (i.e., fewer than five or six levels) "
"should not be used as random effects grouping factors as the number of "
"levels determines the power of the fixed effects tests (Westfall, Kenny, & "
"Judd, 2014). The random effects structure (i.e., random intercepts, random "
"slopes, and correlations among random effects parameters) can be specified "
"under Model - Random effects. The default random effects structure is the "
"automatically determined 'maximal random effects structure justified by the "
"design' (Barr, Levy, Scheepers, & Tily, 2013)."
msgstr ""
"Variabel kategorikal menentukan klaster observasi (yaitu, beberapa observasi "
"per tingkat dari faktor penggrupan efek acak). Ini adalah secara umum "
"variabel, seperti peserta atau item, yang ingin generalisasi. Faktor dengan "
"tingkat sangat sedikit (yaitu, lebih sedikit dari lima atau enam tingkat) "
"tidak harus digunakan sebagai faktor penggrupan efek acak karena jumlah "
"tingkat menentukan kekuatan uji efek tetap (Westfall, Kenny, & Judd, 2014). "
"Struktur efek acak (yaitu, intersep acak, corong acak, dan korelasi si "
"antara parameter efek acak) dapat ditentukan di bawah Model - Efek acak. "
"Struktur efek acak bawaan secara otomatis 'maksimal struktur efek acak "
"maksimal dibenarkan oleh rancangan' ditentukan (Barr, Levy, Scheepers, & "
"Tily, 2013)."

msgctxt "MixedModelsBLMM|"
msgid ""
"Fixed effects variables that can be used for computing estimated marginal "
"means."
msgstr ""
"Variabel efek tetap yang dapat digunakan untuk menghitung rerata margin "
"terestimasi."

msgctxt "MixedModelsBLMM|"
msgid "Variables for which the estimated marginal means will be computed."
msgstr "Variabel untuk mana rerata margin terestimasi akan dihitung."

msgctxt "MixedModelsBLMM|"
msgid ""
"Width of the confidence interval. Set at 95% by default, which can be "
"changed by the user."
msgstr ""
"Lebar interval kepercayaan. Diatur ke 95% secara bawaan, yang dapat diubah "
"oleh pengguna."

msgctxt "MixedModelsBLMM|"
msgid ""
"What should be the 'levels' of continuous variables (expressed in standard "
"deviations) for which the estimated marginal means are computed."
msgstr ""
"Apa seharusnya 'tingkat' dari variabel berkelanjutan (diungkapkan di deviasi "
"standar) yang mana rerata margin terestimasi dihitung."

msgctxt "MixedModelsBLMM|"
msgid ""
"Creates a table for specifying contrasts based on the estimated marginal "
"means. The first column contains row indices corresponding to the estimated "
"marginal means output table. Columns with variable names show the levels of "
"each variable for the respective marginal mean. Columns labeled ‘Contrast x’ "
"are used to define contrasts. To specify a contrast between two marginal "
"means, enter -1 and 1 in the corresponding rows. Interactions can be tested "
"by defining differences in marginal means of one variable across levels of "
"another."
msgstr ""
"Membuat tabel untuk menentukan kontras berdasarkan rerata margin "
"terestimasi. Kolom pertama berisi indeks baris sesuai dengan tabel luaran "
"rerata margin terestimasi. Kolom dengan nama variabel menampilkan tingkat "
"dari setiap variabel untuk rerata margin masing-masing. Kolom dilabeli "
"‘Kontras x’ digunakan untuk mendefinisikan kontras. Untuk menentukan kontras "
"antara dua rerata margin, masukkan -1 dan 1 di baris sesuai. Interaksi dapat "
"diuji dengan mendefinisikan perbedaan di rerata margin dari satu variabel di "
"seluruh tingkat lain."

msgctxt "MixedModelsBLMM|"
msgid "Continuous variables"
msgstr "Variabel berkelanjutan"

msgctxt "MixedModelsBLMM|"
msgid ""
"Continuous fixed effects variables that can be used for estimating the "
"conditional slopes."
msgstr ""
"Variabel efek tetap berkelanjutan yang dapat digunakan untuk mengestimasi "
"corong kondisional."

msgctxt "MixedModelsBLMM|"
msgid "Variables for which the estimated conditional slopes will be computed."
msgstr "Variabel yang mana corong kondisional terestimasi akan dihitung."

msgctxt "MixedModelsBLMM|"
msgid ""
"Fixed effects variables over which the conditional slopes can be computed."
msgstr "Variabel efek tetap di mana corong kondisional dapat dihitung."

msgctxt "MixedModelsBLMM|"
msgid "Variables over which the conditional slopes will be computed."
msgstr "Variabel di mana corong kondisional akan dihitung."

msgctxt "MixedModelsBLMM|"
msgid ""
"What should be the 'levels' of continuous variables (expressed in standard "
"deviations) over which the conditional slopes are computed."
msgstr ""
"Apa seharusnya 'tingkat' dari variabel berkelanjutan (diungkapkan di deviasi "
"standar) di mana corong kondisional dihitung."

msgctxt "MixedModelsBLMM|"
msgid ""
"Creates a table for specifying contrasts based on the estimated conditional "
"slopes. The first column contains row indices corresponding to the estimated "
"conditional slopes output table. Columns with variable names show the levels "
"of each variable for the respective conditional slope. Columns labeled "
"‘Contrast x’ are used to define contrasts. To specify a contrast between two "
"conditional slopes, enter -1 and 1 in the corresponding rows. Interactions "
"can be tested by defining differences in conditional slopes of one variable "
"across levels of another."
msgstr ""
"Membuat tabel untuk menentukan kontras berdasarkan corong kondisional "
"terestimasi. Kolom pertama berisi indeks baris sesuai dengan tabel luaran "
"corong kondisional terestimasi. Kolom dengan nama variabel menampilkan "
"tingkat dari setiap variabel untuk corong kondisional masing-masing. Kolom "
"dilabeli ‘Kontras x’ digunakan untuk menentukan kontras. Untuk menentukan "
"kontras antara dua corong kondisional, masukkan -1 dan 1 di baris sesuai. "
"Interaksi dapat diuji dengan mendefinisikan perbedaan di corong kondisional "
"dari satu variabel di seluruh tingkat lain."

msgctxt "MixedModelsGLMM|"
msgid ""
"Generalized Linear Mixed Models allow you to model a linear relationship "
"between one or more explanatory variable(s) and a dependent variable in "
"cases where the observations are not independent, but clustered within one "
"or several random effects grouping factors (e.g., repeated measures across "
"participants or items, children within schools). They are generalizations of "
"Linear Mixed Models and allow you to model response variables that are not "
"continuous using different likelihoods and link functions."
msgstr ""
"Model Bercampur Linear Tergeneralisasi mengizinkan Anda untuk memodelkan "
"hubungan linear antara satu atau lebih variabel penjelasan dan variabel "
"dependen dalam kasus di mana observasi tidak independen, tetapi diklaster "
"dalam satu atau beberapa faktor penggrupan efek acak (mis., pengukuran "
"berulang di seluruh peserta atau item, anak-anak dalam sekolah). Mereka "
"adalah generalisasi Model Bercampur Linear dan mengizinkan Anda untuk "
"memodelkan variabel tanggapan yang tidak berkelanjutan menggunakan "
"kemungkinan berbeda dan fungsi tautan."

msgctxt "MixedModelsGLMM|"
msgid "Assumptions"
msgstr "Asumsi"

msgctxt "MixedModelsGLMM|"
msgid ""
"Linearity and additivity: The response variable is related to all predictors "
"according to the link function and the effects of the predictors are "
"additive on the linear scale."
msgstr ""
"Linearitas dan penambahan: Variabel tanggapan terkait dengan semua prediktor "
"menurut fungsi tautan dan efek prediktor aditif pada skala linear."

msgctxt "MixedModelsGLMM|"
msgid ""
"Independence of errors: The errors are uncorrelated with each other after "
"taking the model (i.e., fixed effects and random effects structure) into "
"account."
msgstr ""
"Independen dari galat: Galat tidak dikorelasikan satu sama lain setelah "
"mengambil model (yaitu, efek tetap dan struktur efek acak) diperhitungkan."

msgctxt "MixedModelsGLMM|"
msgid ""
"Homoscedasticity: The error variance of each predictor is constant across "
"all values of that predictor."
msgstr ""
"Homosedastisitas: Varians galat dari setiap prediktor konstan di seluruh "
"nilai prediktor itu."

msgctxt "MixedModelsGLMM|"
msgid ""
"Distribution of errors: The errors are distributed according to the "
"distributional family."
msgstr ""
"Distribusi dari galat: Galat didistribusikan menurut keluarga distribusional."

msgctxt "MixedModelsGLMM|"
msgid ""
"The analysis uses sum contrast encoding for categorical (nominal and "
"ordinal) predictors (R uses dummy encoding by default). This scheme is used "
"for better interpretability of models with interactions. However, the fixed "
"and random effects estimates will differ from those obtained from R with "
"default settings. We advise using the 'Estimated marginal means' section for "
"obtaining mean estimates at individual factor levels. For comparing the mean "
"estimates, use the contrasts option. To change the contrast encoding for the "
"analysis use Factor contrast dropdown in the Options section."
msgstr ""
"Analisis menggunakan pengenkodean kontras jumlah untuk prediktor (R "
"menggunakan pengenkodean dummy secara bawaan) kategorikal (nominal dan "
"ordinal). Skema ini digunakan untuk interpretabilitias lebih baik dari model "
"dengan interaksi. Namun, estimasi efek tetap dan acak akan berbeda dari itu "
"diperoleh daru R dengan pengaturan bawaan. Kami menyarankan menggunakan "
"bagian 'Rerata margin terestimasi' untuk memperoleh estimasi rerata di "
"tingkat faktor individu. Untuk membandingkan estimasi rerata, gunakan opsi "
"kontras. Untuk mengubah pengenkodean kontras untuk analisis gunakan tarik "
"turun Kontras faktor di bagian Opsi."

msgctxt "MixedModelsGLMM|"
msgid "The analysis uses a long data format."
msgstr "Analisis menggunakan format data panjang."

msgctxt "MixedModelsGLMM|"
msgid "Dependent (response) variable."
msgstr "Variabel dependen (tanggapan)."

msgctxt "MixedModelsGLMM|"
msgid ""
"Number of trials, only applicable if the Binomial (aggregated) family is "
"selected."
msgstr ""
"Jumlah percobaan, hanya dapat diterapkan jika keluarga Binomial "
"(teragregasi) dipilih."

msgctxt "MixedModelsGLMM|"
msgid ""
"Variables used as the fixed effects predictors (the model terms can be "
"specified under Model section). These are usually the variables of primary "
"scientific interest."
msgstr ""
"Variabel digunakan sebagai prediktor efek tetap (istilah model dapat "
"ditentukan di bawah bagian Model). Ini biasanya variabel dari fokus utama "
"saintifik."

msgctxt "MixedModelsGLMM|"
msgid ""
"Categorical variable(s) specifying clusters of observations (i.e., several "
"observations per level of a random effects grouping factor). These are "
"typically variables, such as participants or items, one wants to generalize "
"over. Factors with very few levels (i.e., fewer than five or six levels) "
"should not be used as random effects grouping factors as the number of "
"levels determines the power of the fixed effects tests (Westfall, Kenny, & "
"Judd, 2014). The random effects structure (i.e., random intercepts, random "
"slopes, and correlations among random effects parameters) can be specified "
"under Model - Random effects. The default random effects structure is the "
"automatically determined 'maximal random effects structure justified by the "
"design' (Barr, Levy, Scheepers, & Tily, 2013)."
msgstr ""
"Variabel kategorikal menentukan klaster observasi (yaitu, beberapa observasi "
"per tingkat dari faktor penggrupan efek acak). Ini adalah secara umum "
"variabel, seperti peserta atau item, yang ingin generalisasi. Faktor dengan "
"tingkat sangat sedikit (yaitu, lebih sedikit dari lima atau enam tingkat) "
"tidak harus digunakan sebagai faktor penggrupan efek acak karena jumlah "
"tingkat menentukan kekuatan uji efek tetap (Westfall, Kenny, & Judd, 2014). "
"Struktur efek acak (yaitu, intersep acak, corong acak, dan korelasi si "
"antara parameter efek acak) dapat ditentukan di bawah Model - Efek acak. "
"Struktur efek acak bawaan secara otomatis 'maksimal struktur efek acak "
"maksimal dibenarkan oleh rancangan' ditentukan (Barr, Levy, Scheepers, & "
"Tily, 2013)."

msgctxt "MixedModelsGLMM|"
msgid ""
"Distribution function whose likelihood will be used for the dependent "
"variable. Several options are available."
msgstr ""
"Fungsi distribusi yang kemungkinan akan digunakan untuk variabel dependen. "
"Beberapa opsi tersedia."

msgctxt "MixedModelsGLMM|"
msgid ""
"Link function that will be used to model the mean parameter of the selected "
"distribution function."
msgstr ""
"Fungsi tautan yang akan digunakan untuk memodelkan parameter rerata dari "
"fungsi distribusi terpilih."

msgctxt "MixedModelsGLMM|"
msgid ""
"Fixed effects variables that can be used for computing estimated marginal "
"means."
msgstr ""
"Variabel efek tetap yang dapat digunakan untuk menghitung rerata margin "
"terestimasi."

msgctxt "MixedModelsGLMM|"
msgid "Variables for which the estimated marginal means will be computed."
msgstr "Variabel untuk mana rerata margin terestimasi akan dihitung."

msgctxt "MixedModelsGLMM|"
msgid ""
"Width of the confidence interval. Set at 95% by default, which can be "
"changed by the user."
msgstr ""
"Lebar interval kepercayaan. Diatur ke 95% secara bawaan, yang dapat diubah "
"oleh pengguna."

msgctxt "MixedModelsGLMM|"
msgid ""
"Specifies the 'levels' of continuous variables (expressed in standard "
"deviations) over which the estimated marginal means are computed."
msgstr ""
"Menentukan 'tingkat' dari variabel berkelanjutan (diungkapkan di deviasi "
"standar) di mana rerata margin terestimasi dihitung."

msgctxt "MixedModelsGLMM|"
msgid "Value to which the estimated marginal means will be compared."
msgstr "Nilai mana rerata margin terestimasi akan dibandingkan."

msgctxt "MixedModelsGLMM|"
msgid ""
"Whether the estimated marginal means should be computed on the response "
"scale or untransformed linear scale. The response scale is selected by "
"default."
msgstr ""
"Apakah rerata margin terestimasi harus dihitung pada skala tanggapan atau "
"skala linear tidak bertransform. Skala tanggapan dipilih secara bawaan."

msgctxt "MixedModelsGLMM|"
msgid ""
"Creates a table for specifying contrasts based on the estimated marginal "
"means. The first column contains row indices corresponding to the estimated "
"marginal means output table. Columns with variable names show the levels of "
"each variable for the respective marginal mean. Columns labeled ‘Contrast x’ "
"are used to define contrasts. To specify a contrast between two marginal "
"means, enter -1 and 1 in the corresponding rows. Interactions can be tested "
"by defining differences in marginal means of one variable across levels of "
"another."
msgstr ""
"Membuat tabel untuk menentukan kontras berdasarkan rerata margin "
"terestimasi. Kolom pertama berisi indeks baris sesuai dengan tabel luaran "
"rerata margin terestimasi. Kolom dengan nama variabel menampilkan tingkat "
"dari setiap variabel untuk rerata margin masing-masing. Kolom dilabeli "
"‘Kontras x’ digunakan untuk mendefinisikan kontras. Untuk menentukan kontras "
"antara dua rerata margin, masukkan -1 dan 1 di baris sesuai. Interaksi dapat "
"diuji dengan mendefinisikan perbedaan di rerata margin dari satu variabel di "
"seluruh tingkat lain."

msgctxt "MixedModelsGLMM|"
msgid ""
"To correct for multiple comparison testing and avoid Type I errors, "
"different methods for correcting the p-value are available."
msgstr ""
"Untuk mengoreksi untuk beberapa pengujian perbandingan dan menghindari galat "
"Jenis I, metode berbeda untuk mengoreksi nilai-p tersedia."

msgctxt "MixedModelsGLMM|"
msgid ""
"This method is also called sequential Bonferroni, and is considered less "
"conservative than the Bonferroni method."
msgstr ""
"Metode ini juga disebut sekuensial Bonferroni, dan dianggap kurang "
"konservatif dari metode Bonferroni."

msgctxt "MixedModelsGLMM|"
msgid ""
"Correction that takes into account that test results might be correlated. "
"Best suited for multivariate models."
msgstr ""
"Koreksi yang memperhitungkan bahwa hasil uji mungkin dikorelasi. Paling "
"cocok untuk model multivariat."

msgctxt "MixedModelsGLMM|"
msgid ""
"Adjusting significance levels in a linear regression, to account for "
"multiple comparisons. This method is considered to be quite conservative."
msgstr ""
"Menyesuaikan tingkat signifikan di regresi linear, untuk memperhitungkan "
"beberapa perbandingan. Metode ini dianggap cukup konservatif."

msgctxt "MixedModelsGLMM|"
msgid ""
"Compare all possible pairs of group means. This correction can be used when "
"the groups of the independent variable have an equal sample size and "
"variance."
msgstr ""
"Bandingkan semua pasangan rerata grup memungkinkan. Koreksi ini dapat "
"digunakan ketika grup variabel independen memiliki ukuran sampel dan varians "
"sama."

msgctxt "MixedModelsGLMM|"
msgid "No adjustment is conducted."
msgstr "Tidak ada penyesuaian diadakan."

msgctxt "MixedModelsGLMM|"
msgid ""
"This correction is considered conservative. The risk of Type I error is "
"reduced, however, the statistical power decreases as well."
msgstr ""
"Koreksi ini dianggap konservatif. Risiko galat Jenis I dikurangi, namun, "
"kekuatan statistik menurun juga."

msgctxt "MixedModelsGLMM|"
msgid ""
"This correction is considered to be more powerful but less conservative than "
"Bonferroni and Holm corrections. Recommended for a small number of tests."
msgstr ""
"Koreksi ini dianggap lebih kuat tetapi kurang konservatif dari koreksi "
"Bonferroni dan Holm. Direkomendasikan untuk jumlah uji kecil."

msgctxt "MixedModelsGLMM|"
msgid "Continuous variables"
msgstr "Variabel berkelanjutan"

msgctxt "MixedModelsGLMM|"
msgid ""
"Continuous fixed effects variables that can be used for estimating the "
"conditional slopes."
msgstr ""
"Variabel efek tetap berkelanjutan yang dapat digunakan untuk mengestimasi "
"corong kondisional."

msgctxt "MixedModelsGLMM|"
msgid "Variables for which the estimated conditional slopes will be computed."
msgstr "Variabel yang mana corong kondisional terestimasi akan dihitung."

msgctxt "MixedModelsGLMM|"
msgid ""
"Fixed effects variables over which the conditional slopes can be computed."
msgstr "Variabel efek tetap di mana corong kondisional dapat dihitung."

msgctxt "MixedModelsGLMM|"
msgid "Variables over which the conditional slopes will be computed."
msgstr "Variabel di mana corong kondisional akan dihitung."

msgctxt "MixedModelsGLMM|"
msgid ""
"Specifies the 'levels' of continuous variables (expressed in standard "
"deviations) over which the conditional slopes are computed."
msgstr ""
"Menentukan 'tingkat' dari variabel berkelanjutan (diungkapkan di deviasi "
"standar) di mana corong kondisional dihitung."

msgctxt "MixedModelsGLMM|"
msgid "Value to which the estimated conditional slopes will be compared."
msgstr "Nilai yang mana corong kondisional terestimasi akan dibandingkan."

msgctxt "MixedModelsGLMM|"
msgid ""
"Creates a table for specifying contrasts based on the estimated conditional "
"slopes. The first column contains row indices corresponding to the estimated "
"conditional slopes output table. Columns with variable names show the levels "
"of each variable for the respective conditional slope. Columns labeled "
"‘Contrast x’ are used to define contrasts. To specify a contrast between two "
"conditional slopes, enter -1 and 1 in the corresponding rows. Interactions "
"can be tested by defining differences in conditional slopes of one variable "
"across levels of another."
msgstr ""
"Membuat tabel untuk menentukan kontras berdasarkan corong kondisional "
"terestimasi. Kolom pertama berisi indeks baris sesuai dengan tabel luaran "
"corong kondisional terestimasi. Kolom dengan nama variabel menampilkan "
"tingkat dari setiap variabel untuk corong kondisional masing-masing. Kolom "
"dilabeli ‘Kontras x’ digunakan untuk menentukan kontras. Untuk menentukan "
"kontras antara dua corong kondisional, masukkan -1 dan 1 di baris sesuai. "
"Interaksi dapat diuji dengan mendefinisikan perbedaan di corong kondisional "
"dari satu variabel di seluruh tingkat lain."

msgctxt "MixedModelsLMM|"
msgid ""
"Linear Mixed Models allow you to model a linear relationship between one or "
"more explanatory variable(s) and a continuous dependent variable in cases "
"where the observations are not independent, but clustered within one or "
"several random effects grouping factors (e.g., repeated measures across "
"participants or items, children within schools). An introduction to this "
"model class and the concepts introduced below is provided in Singmann and "
"Kellen (2019)."
msgstr ""
"Model Bercampur Linear mengizinkan Anda untuk memodelkan hubungan linear "
"antara satu atau lebih variabel penjelasan dan variabel dependen "
"berkelanjutan dalam kasus di mana observasi tidak independen, tetapi "
"diklaster dalam satu atau beberapa faktor penggrupan efek acak (mis., "
"pengukuran berulang di seluruh peserta atau item, anak-anak dalam sekolah). "
"Pengenalan kelas model ini dan konsep dikenalkan di bawah disediakan di "
"Singmann dan Kellen (2019)."

msgctxt "MixedModelsLMM|"
msgid "Assumptions"
msgstr "Asumsi"

msgctxt "MixedModelsLMM|"
msgid "Continuous response variable."
msgstr "Variabel tanggapan berkelanjutan."

msgctxt "MixedModelsLMM|"
msgid ""
"Linearity and additivity: The response variable is linearly related to all "
"predictors and the effects of the predictors are additive."
msgstr ""
"Linearitas dan penambahan: Variabel tanggapan secara linear terkait dengan "
"semua prediktor dan efek prediktor aditif."

msgctxt "MixedModelsLMM|"
msgid ""
"Independence of errors: The errors are uncorrelated with each other after "
"taking the model (i.e., fixed effects and random effects structure) into "
"account."
msgstr ""
"Independen dari galat: Galat tidak dikorelasikan satu sama lain setelah "
"mengambil model (yaitu, efek tetap dan struktur efek acak) diperhitungkan."

msgctxt "MixedModelsLMM|"
msgid ""
"Homoscedasticity: The error variance of each predictor is constant across "
"all values of that predictor."
msgstr ""
"Homosedastisitas: Varians galat dari setiap prediktor konstan di seluruh "
"nilai prediktor itu."

msgctxt "MixedModelsLMM|"
msgid ""
"Normality of errors: The errors are normally distributed with mean zero."
msgstr ""
"Normalitas dari galat: Galat secara normal didistribusikan dengan rerata nol."

msgctxt "MixedModelsLMM|"
msgid ""
"The analysis uses sum contrast encoding for categorical (nominal and "
"ordinal) predictors (R uses dummy encoding by default). This scheme is used "
"for better interpretability of models with interactions. However, the fixed "
"and random effects estimates will differ from those obtained from R with "
"default settings. We advise using the 'Estimated marginal means' section for "
"obtaining mean estimates at individual factor levels. For comparing the mean "
"estimates, use the contrasts option. To change the contrast encoding for the "
"analysis use Factor contrast dropdown in the Options section."
msgstr ""
"Analisis menggunakan pengenkodean kontras jumlah untuk prediktor (R "
"menggunakan pengenkodean dummy secara bawaan) kategorikal (nominal dan "
"ordinal). Skema ini digunakan untuk interpretabilitias lebih baik dari model "
"dengan interaksi. Namun, estimasi efek tetap dan acak akan berbeda dari itu "
"diperoleh daru R dengan pengaturan bawaan. Kami menyarankan menggunakan "
"bagian 'Rerata margin terestimasi' untuk memperoleh estimasi rerata di "
"tingkat faktor individu. Untuk membandingkan estimasi rerata, gunakan opsi "
"kontras. Untuk mengubah pengenkodean kontras untuk analisis gunakan tarik "
"turun Kontras faktor di bagian Opsi."

msgctxt "MixedModelsLMM|"
msgid "The analysis uses a long data format."
msgstr "Analisis menggunakan format data panjang."

msgctxt "MixedModelsLMM|"
msgid "Dependent (response) variable."
msgstr "Variabel dependen (tanggapan)."

msgctxt "MixedModelsLMM|"
msgid ""
"Variables used as the fixed effects predictors (the model terms can be "
"specified under Model section). These are usually the variables of primary "
"scientific interest."
msgstr ""
"Variabel digunakan sebagai prediktor efek tetap (istilah model dapat "
"ditentukan di bawah bagian Model). Ini biasanya variabel dari fokus utama "
"saintifik."

msgctxt "MixedModelsLMM|"
msgid ""
"Categorical variable(s) specifying clusters of observations (i.e., several "
"observations per level of a random effects grouping factor). These are "
"typically variables, such as participants or items, one wants to generalize "
"over. Factors with very few levels (i.e., fewer than five or six levels) "
"should not be used as random effects grouping factors as the number of "
"levels determines the power of the fixed effects tests (Westfall, Kenny, & "
"Judd, 2014). The random effects structure (i.e., random intercepts, random "
"slopes, and correlations among random effects parameters) can be specified "
"under Model - Random effects. The default random effects structure is the "
"automatically determined 'maximal random effects structure justified by the "
"design' (Barr, Levy, Scheepers, & Tily, 2013)."
msgstr ""
"Variabel kategorikal menentukan klaster observasi (yaitu, beberapa observasi "
"per tingkat dari faktor penggrupan efek acak). Ini adalah secara umum "
"variabel, seperti peserta atau item, yang ingin generalisasi. Faktor dengan "
"tingkat sangat sedikit (yaitu, lebih sedikit dari lima atau enam tingkat) "
"tidak harus digunakan sebagai faktor penggrupan efek acak karena jumlah "
"tingkat menentukan kekuatan uji efek tetap (Westfall, Kenny, & Judd, 2014). "
"Struktur efek acak (yaitu, intersep acak, corong acak, dan korelasi si "
"antara parameter efek acak) dapat ditentukan di bawah Model - Efek acak. "
"Struktur efek acak bawaan secara otomatis 'maksimal struktur efek acak "
"maksimal dibenarkan oleh rancangan' ditentukan (Barr, Levy, Scheepers, & "
"Tily, 2013)."

msgctxt "MixedModelsLMM|"
msgid ""
"Fixed effects variables that can be used for computing estimated marginal "
"means."
msgstr ""
"Variabel efek tetap yang dapat digunakan untuk menghitung rerata margin "
"terestimasi."

msgctxt "MixedModelsLMM|"
msgid "Variables for which the estimated marginal means will be computed."
msgstr "Variabel untuk mana rerata margin terestimasi akan dihitung."

msgctxt "MixedModelsLMM|"
msgid ""
"Width of the confidence interval. Set at 95% by default, which can be "
"changed by the user."
msgstr ""
"Lebar interval kepercayaan. Diatur ke 95% secara bawaan, yang dapat diubah "
"oleh pengguna."

msgctxt "MixedModelsLMM|"
msgid ""
"Specifies the 'levels' of continuous variables (expressed in standard "
"deviations) over which the estimated marginal means are computed."
msgstr ""
"Menentukan 'tingkat' dari variabel berkelanjutan (diungkapkan di deviasi "
"standar) di mana rerata margin terestimasi dihitung."

msgctxt "MixedModelsLMM|"
msgid ""
"Method of estimating degrees of freedom. Note that Kenward-Roger "
"approximation for degrees of freedom can be very RAM and time consuming with "
"larger datasets. There are 3 available options."
msgstr ""
"Metode dari mengestimasi derajat kebebasan. Dicatat bahwa perkiraan Kenward-"
"Roger untuk derajat kebebasan dapat lebih RAM dan mengonsumsi waktu dengan "
"rangkaian data lebih besar. Ada 3 opsi tersedia."

msgctxt "MixedModelsLMM|"
msgid ""
"JASP automatically uses Asymptotic degrees of freedom in cases with a large "
"dataset. This can be disabled by ticking this checkbox."
msgstr ""
"JASP secara otomatis menggunakan derajat kebebasan Asimptotik di kasus "
"dengan rangkaian data besar. Ini dapat dinonaktifkan dengan mencentang kotak "
"centang ini."

msgctxt "MixedModelsLMM|"
msgid "Value to which the estimated marginal means will be compared."
msgstr "Nilai mana rerata margin terestimasi akan dibandingkan."

msgctxt "MixedModelsLMM|"
msgid ""
"Creates a table for specifying contrasts based on the estimated marginal "
"means. The first column contains row indices corresponding to the estimated "
"marginal means output table. Columns with variable names show the levels of "
"each variable for the respective marginal mean. Columns labeled ‘Contrast x’ "
"are used to define contrasts. To specify a contrast between two marginal "
"means, enter -1 and 1 in the corresponding rows. Interactions can be tested "
"by defining differences in marginal means of one variable across levels of "
"another."
msgstr ""
"Membuat tabel untuk menentukan kontras berdasarkan rerata margin "
"terestimasi. Kolom pertama berisi indeks baris sesuai dengan tabel luaran "
"rerata margin terestimasi. Kolom dengan nama variabel menampilkan tingkat "
"dari setiap variabel untuk rerata margin masing-masing. Kolom dilabeli "
"‘Kontras x’ digunakan untuk mendefinisikan kontras. Untuk menentukan kontras "
"antara dua rerata margin, masukkan -1 dan 1 di baris sesuai. Interaksi dapat "
"diuji dengan mendefinisikan perbedaan di rerata margin dari satu variabel di "
"seluruh tingkat lain."

msgctxt "MixedModelsLMM|"
msgid ""
"To correct for multiple comparison testing and avoid Type I errors, "
"different methods for correcting the p-value are available."
msgstr ""
"Untuk mengoreksi untuk beberapa pengujian perbandingan dan menghindari galat "
"Jenis I, metode berbeda untuk mengoreksi nilai-p tersedia."

msgctxt "MixedModelsLMM|"
msgid ""
"This method is also called sequential Bonferroni, and is considered less "
"conservative than the Bonferroni method."
msgstr ""
"Metode ini juga disebut sekuensial Bonferroni, dan dianggap kurang "
"konservatif dari metode Bonferroni."

msgctxt "MixedModelsLMM|"
msgid ""
"Correction that takes into account that test results might be correlated. "
"Best suited for multivariate models."
msgstr ""
"Koreksi yang memperhitungkan bahwa hasil uji mungkin dikorelasi. Paling "
"cocok untuk model multivariat."

msgctxt "MixedModelsLMM|"
msgid ""
"Adjusting significance levels in a linear regression, to account for "
"multiple comparisons. This method is considered to be quite conservative."
msgstr ""
"Menyesuaikan tingkat signifikan di regresi linear, untuk memperhitungkan "
"beberapa perbandingan. Metode ini dianggap cukup konservatif."

msgctxt "MixedModelsLMM|"
msgid ""
"Compare all possible pairs of group means. This correction can be used when "
"the groups of the independent variable have an equal sample size and "
"variance."
msgstr ""
"Bandingkan semua pasangan rerata grup memungkinkan. Koreksi ini dapat "
"digunakan ketika grup variabel independen memiliki ukuran sampel dan varians "
"sama."

msgctxt "MixedModelsLMM|"
msgid "No adjustment is conducted."
msgstr "Tidak ada penyesuaian diadakan."

msgctxt "MixedModelsLMM|"
msgid ""
"This correction is considered conservative. The risk of Type I error is "
"reduced, however, the statistical power decreases as well."
msgstr ""
"Koreksi ini dianggap konservatif. Risiko galat Jenis I dikurangi, namun, "
"kekuatan statistik menurun juga."

msgctxt "MixedModelsLMM|"
msgid ""
"This correction is considered to be more powerful but less conservative than "
"Bonferroni and Holm corrections. Recommended for a small number of tests."
msgstr ""
"Koreksi ini dianggap lebih kuat tetapi kurang konservatif dari koreksi "
"Bonferroni dan Holm. Direkomendasikan untuk jumlah uji kecil."

msgctxt "MixedModelsLMM|"
msgid "Continuous variables"
msgstr "Variabel berkelanjutan"

msgctxt "MixedModelsLMM|"
msgid ""
"Continuous fixed effects variables that can be used for estimating the "
"conditional slopes."
msgstr ""
"Variabel efek tetap berkelanjutan yang dapat digunakan untuk mengestimasi "
"corong kondisional."

msgctxt "MixedModelsLMM|"
msgid "Variables for which the estimated conditional slopes will be computed."
msgstr "Variabel yang mana corong kondisional terestimasi akan dihitung."

msgctxt "MixedModelsLMM|"
msgid ""
"Fixed effects variables over which the conditional slopes can be computed."
msgstr "Variabel efek tetap di mana corong kondisional dapat dihitung."

msgctxt "MixedModelsLMM|"
msgid "Variables over which the conditional slopes will be computed."
msgstr "Variabel di mana corong kondisional akan dihitung."

msgctxt "MixedModelsLMM|"
msgid ""
"Specifies the 'levels' of continuous variables (expressed in standard "
"deviations) over which the conditional slopes are computed."
msgstr ""
"Menentukan 'tingkat' dari variabel berkelanjutan (diungkapkan di deviasi "
"standar) di mana corong kondisional dihitung."

msgctxt "MixedModelsLMM|"
msgid "Value to which the estimated conditional slopes will be compared."
msgstr "Nilai yang mana corong kondisional terestimasi akan dibandingkan."

msgctxt "MixedModelsLMM|"
msgid ""
"Creates a table for specifying contrasts based on the estimated conditional "
"slopes. The first column contains row indices corresponding to the estimated "
"conditional slopes output table. Columns with variable names show the levels "
"of each variable for the respective conditional slope. Columns labeled "
"‘Contrast x’ are used to define contrasts. To specify a contrast between two "
"conditional slopes, enter -1 and 1 in the corresponding rows. Interactions "
"can be tested by defining differences in conditional slopes of one variable "
"across levels of another."
msgstr ""
"Membuat tabel untuk menentukan kontras berdasarkan corong kondisional "
"terestimasi. Kolom pertama berisi indeks baris sesuai dengan tabel luaran "
"corong kondisional terestimasi. Kolom dengan nama variabel menampilkan "
"tingkat dari setiap variabel untuk corong kondisional masing-masing. Kolom "
"dilabeli ‘Kontras x’ digunakan untuk menentukan kontras. Untuk menentukan "
"kontras antara dua corong kondisional, masukkan -1 dan 1 di baris sesuai. "
"Interaksi dapat diuji dengan mendefinisikan perbedaan di corong kondisional "
"dari satu variabel di seluruh tingkat lain."

msgctxt "MixedModelsLMM|"
msgid ""
"To correct for multiple comparison testing and avoid Type I errors, "
"different methods for correcting the p-value are available:"
msgstr ""
"Untuk mengoreksi untuk beberapa pengujian perbandingan dan menghindari galat "
"Jenis I, metode berbeda untuk mengoreksi nilai-p tersedia:"
